---
export const prerender = true;

import Base from '@layouts/Base.astro';
import PageHero from '@components/site/PageHero.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy | Crooked River Ranch RV Park';
const description = 'How Crooked River Ranch RV Park collects, uses, shares, and safeguards information across the website, forms, maps, analytics, and reservation services.';
const canonical = 'https://www.crookedriverranchrv.com/privacy';
---
<Base title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical} ogImage="https://www.crookedriverranchrv.com/images/canyon_day.jpg" heroImagePreload="/images/canyon_day.webp">
  <main id="main-content">
    <PageHero
      eyebrow="Privacy"
      headline="What the site collects."
      accent="Why it is used."
      body="A plain-language overview of information submitted by guests, technical website data, and the services involved in reservations and park operations."
      image="/images/canyon_day.webp"
      imageMobile="/images/canyon_day-mobile.webp"
      imageJpg="/images/canyon_day.jpg"
      alt="Crooked River canyon in daylight"
      caption="Last updated July 19, 2026"
    />
    <section class="crr-section crr-section-soft">
      <div class="v2-shell crr-legal-shell">
        <aside class="crr-legal-aside">
          <strong>Crooked River Ranch C&MA</strong>
          <p>DBA Crooked River Ranch RV Park<br />14875 SW Hays Lane<br />Terrebonne, OR 97760</p>
          <a href="tel:+15419231441">541-923-1441</a>
        </aside>
        <article class="crr-prose">
          <h2>Privacy policy</h2>
          <p><strong>Last updated: July 19, 2026</strong></p>
          <p>Crooked River Ranch Club and Maintenance Association, doing business as Crooked River Ranch RV Park, uses information to operate this website, respond to guests, review applications, manage reservations, maintain park content, and improve the guest experience.</p>

          <h2>Information you provide</h2>
          <p>When you call, submit a website form, apply for a monthly stay, or make a reservation, information may include your name, contact details, stay dates, RV and vehicle details, occupants, pets, emergency contact, application history, messages, and other information you choose to provide.</p>
          <p>Monthly applications may include information used for identity, eligibility, and background-review steps. Do not submit payment-card information through a general website form.</p>

          <h2>Reservations and availability</h2>
          <p>Firefly Reservations handles the guest reservation and payment flow. Rimrock provides availability information displayed by this website. Information submitted to those services is also governed by their respective terms and privacy practices. A reservation is confirmed only through the reservation system and confirmation process.</p>

          <h2>Website and analytics information</h2>
          <p>The website and its service providers may process IP address, device and browser details, pages viewed, referral information, interaction events, approximate location, timestamps, and diagnostic data. The site currently uses services that can include Netlify hosting and forms, Microsoft Clarity, Google Tag Manager, Google Maps and Places, and Google Fonts. These services may use cookies, local storage, pixels, or comparable technologies according to their own configurations and policies.</p>

          <h2>Operational services</h2>
          <p>Supabase supports website data, authentication, and media storage. Zoho supports park calendar and media workflows. Google supports maps, place details, directions, and fonts. Netlify supports hosting, deployments, security, and form processing. These providers process information needed to deliver their services.</p>
          <p>The guest-review and guest-photo sections request current public content from Google Places when they approach view. Those responses can include review text, ratings, dates, photographs, author names, public profile links, profile images, source links, and reporting links. The website does not save or substitute that content; each displayed review and photograph remains linked and attributed to Google Maps and its contributor.</p>
          <p><strong>Google Business Profile authorization.</strong> Crooked River Ranch RV Park Website uses an OAuth connection authorized by a park listing owner to read public customer media associated with the park’s Google Business Profile. The connection is used to retrieve public visitor photographs and the attribution information needed to display them accurately on this website. The website does not use this authorization to create, alter, or delete reviews or customer photographs, and OAuth credentials are never sent to website visitors.</p>

          <h2>How information is used</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>Respond to questions and support requests</li>
            <li>Review stay applications and coordinate next steps</li>
            <li>Show live site availability and hand off a reservation</li>
            <li>Operate, secure, diagnose, and improve the website</li>
            <li>Maintain park maps, event information, and local guides</li>
            <li>Meet legal, safety, accounting, and operational obligations</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Sharing and sale</h2>
          <p>Information is shared with service providers when needed to operate the website, process a form or reservation, maintain systems, or meet a legal obligation. The park does not sell personal information for money. Analytics or advertising-related processing may be treated differently under some privacy laws; contact the park with a request or question about applicable rights.</p>

          <h2>Retention and security</h2>
          <p>Information is retained for the period reasonably needed for the purpose collected, operational records, dispute resolution, safety, accounting, and legal obligations. Reasonable safeguards are used, but no internet transmission or storage system can be guaranteed completely secure.</p>

          <h2>Your choices and requests</h2>
          <p>Depending on applicable law, you may request access, correction, deletion, or information about processing. Some records may need to be retained for legal or operational reasons. Contact the park at 541-923-1441 or by mail at the address shown on this page.</p>

          <h2>Children and changes</h2>
          <p>The website is not directed to children under 13, and the park does not knowingly collect their personal information through the website without appropriate authorization. This policy may be updated as services or practices change; the date above identifies the current version.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
